> look at the exception code. `processCodeTaskNameCodeEntry` shouldn't be null. And when `processCodeTaskNameCodeEntry.getValue()` is null ,it should be return `0L`. I can't figure how to happened. My branchâ€˜s version is 2.0.5-release and I have checked the code is same with above from the compiled jar . Could you have a look at here, please. @JinyLeeChina

I found the reason! Firstly, the NPE cause by `long` can't be null. Maybe  it should replaced by `Long`. 
When the task A was depended by a sub process 's task B, task A rename to A1, or be deleted. And the task B 's depend item list wouldn't update, then cause the result that can't find the `depTasks`.
It would be ok with fix the dependent task by manual.
